<emphasis bold="true" box="[183,317,641,675]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">Breeding.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[180,655,680,714]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="13.[180,1389,254,912]" box="[180,655,680,714]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[180,416,680,714]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="610" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[180,1389,254,912]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[182,886,721,755]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Little is known, but populations of Kilonzo’s Brush-furred Rats decline from dry to rainy seasons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="610" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="13.[180,1389,254,912]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[183,529,799,833]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not yet assessed on The IUCN Red List. Kilonzo’s Brush-furred Rat is rarely captured.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
